prompt:
Add a public function called Divide to Contracts.calr that divides two numbers with a custom error message for the precondition. It takes i32 parameters a and b and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor custom error message syntax:
§F{f001:Divide:pub}
  §I{i32:a}
  §I{i32:b}
  §O{i32}
  §Q{"Divisor must not be zero"} (!= b 0)
  §R (/ a b)
§/F{f001}

The §Q{"message"} (condition) syntax adds a custom error message:
- The message in quotes is shown when the contract fails
- Helps with debugging and documentation
- Works for both §Q (precondition) and §S (postcondition)
